The brine shrimp lethality assay was used with slight modification as described by Fatima et al. [57] using artificial sea water with a salinity of 35 g/L [58] and brine shrimps, and nanoparticles. The assay was performed in serial dilution (400, 200, 100, 50, and 25 µg/mL). The samples were introduced to the 96 well plates and the prepared sea water was added to the respective well contained the tested samples. For the experiment, DMSO was chosen as the negative control while doxorubicin was used as the positive control. After that, it was put in a suitable environment with an adequate amount of light and oxygen. After a day, the number of live and dead shrimp was counted using the following Eq. (5).
